A small explosive eruption occurred at Mount St. Helens, generating a plume of steam and ash.
Scientists are closely monitoring the volcano for signs of a larger eruption.
Tourists flocked to witness the activity, but were evacuated as seismic activity increased.
The recent tremors suggest new magma entering the volcano, raising concerns of a potential larger explosion.
Despite the heightened activity, experts believe the threat of a major eruption is low.
Residents near the volcano remain cautious but prepared, recalling the devastation caused by the 1980 eruption.
The situation is being closely monitored to ensure public safety.
